name: Starlink Group 6-12
details: SpaceX's Falcon 9 rocket will launch 22 Starlink satellites to low Earth orbit from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida.

name: Crew-7 Mission
details: SpaceX's Dragon spacecraft will carry four astronauts to the International Space Station as part of NASA's Commercial Crew Program.

name: Polaris Dawn
details: The first of three human spaceflights as part of the Polaris Program, which will include the first commercial spacewalk and testing of Starlink laser-based communications.

name: Starship Orbital Test Flight
details: SpaceX plans to conduct another test flight of its fully reusable Starship vehicle, aiming to reach orbital velocity.
